			<p>3. <strong>Complexity:</strong> Can you uncover the complexities of Madoka Kaname and Revy in above images? In old anime, characters like Madoka Kaname and Motoko Kusanagi searched for who they were, and people around the world connected with them. But in new anime, heroes like Revy and Lucy Heartfilia show more of their challenges and feelings. They're not just perfect—they're like us, with problems and emotions we can understand. </p>

			<p>4. <strong>Breaking Stereotypes:</strong> Imagine Usagi Tsukino next to Mikasa Ackerman. How are they different from what you'd expect? Old heroines like Usagi Tsukino and Belldandy were very feminine and graceful, but new heroes like Mikasa Ackerman and Revy break the usual ideas about how girls should act. They're not waiting for someone else to rescue them—they're strong and capable, of saving themselves and others </p>

			<p>5. <strong>Inspiring Change:</strong> Look into the hearts of Sakura Kinomoto and Yona. What do you see? They're not just characters in a show—they give us hope, show us how to keep going when things are tough, and push us to make a difference. They inspire us to be courageous, to fight for what's fair, and to remember that girls with dreams can change the world </p>

